<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10902] Skip saved cache directory when checking SSTables at startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10902</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SSTable StartupCheck looks for all files which end with &quot;*.db&quot; and compares the version. This causes problems if &lt;tt&gt;saved_cache_directory&lt;/tt&gt; is a subdirectory of a &lt;tt&gt;data_file_directories&lt;/tt&gt;. We should make sure that we are not checking any subdirectory where we might be writing *.db files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is the cause of not being able to restart in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10821&quot; title=&quot;OOM Killer terminates Cassandra when Compactions use too much memory then won&amp;#39;t restart&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10821&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10821&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
